# Environment Variables

# Google Maps API Keys
# 
# SETUP INSTRUCTIONS:
# 1. Go to: https://console.cloud.google.com/google/maps-apis
# 2. Create a new project or select an existing one
# 3. Enable the following APIs:
#    - Places API (for location search in "Add Place" and "Find Ride")
#    - Directions API (for route calculation and fare estimates)
# 4. Create credentials (API Key) under "Credentials" tab
# 5. Copy the same API key for both PLACES and DIRECTIONS below
# 6. (Recommended) Restrict your API key:
#    - API restrictions: Limit to Places API and Directions API only
#    - Application restrictions: Set to your production domain/app
# 
# NOTE: Without valid API keys, location search and saved places will not work
EXPO_PUBLIC_PLACES_API_KEY=your_google_places_api_key_here
EXPO_PUBLIC_DIRECTIONS_API_KEY=your_google_directions_api_key_here
EXPO_PUBLIC_GEOAPIFY_API_KEY=your_geoapify_api_key_here

# Backend API URL (defaults to Render deployment if not set)
# For local development, set to your machine IP:
# EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://192.168.1.100:5000
# For production, leave unset (uses EXPO_PUBLIC_PRODUCTION_API_URL or the default Render URL)
EXPO_PUBLIC_PRODUCTION_API_URL=https://reidehail-backend.onrender.com
